{"symbol": "MEAF6", "uniprot": "Q9HAF1", "protein_name": "Chromatin modification-related protein MEAF6", "length": 191, "function": "Component of the NuA4 histone acetyltransferase complex which is involved in transcriptional activation of select genes principally by acetylation of nucleosomal histone H4 and H2A (PubMed:14966270). This modification may both alter nucleosome - DNA interactions and promote interaction of the modified histones with other proteins which positively regulate transcription (PubMed:14966270). Component of HBO1 complexes, which specifically mediate acetylation of histone H3 at 'Lys-14' (H3K14ac), and have reduced activity toward histone H4 (PubMed:16387653, PubMed:24065767). Component of the MOZ/MORF complex which has a histone H3 acetyltransferase activity (PubMed:18794358)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000163875", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.2528, "protein_drug": 0.54, "rna_drug": 0.559}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.68", "sirna_score": "0.448", "aso_score": "0.464"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/MEAF6.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.832, "volume": 370.3, "residues": [40, 43, 44, 47, 57, 61, 89]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.01, "volume": 82.6, "residues": [44, 47, 48, 57, 58, 86, 87, 88, 89]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.005, "volume": 186.5, "residues": [33, 36, 37, 40, 89, 90, 92, 93, 96]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q9HAF1"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/entry/Q9HAF1"}, {"key": "opentargets", "label": "Open Targets", "url": "https://platform.opentargets.org/target/ENSG00000163875"}, {"key": "genecards", "label": "GeneCards", "url": "https://www.genecards.org/cgi-bin/carddisp.pl?gene=MEAF6"}, {"key": "